            <title>[SOLR-751] WordDelimiterFilter doesn&apos;t adjust startOffset</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-751</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the first character of a token gets stripped the startOffset of that token is not adjusted. With the last character it behaves as expected. I&apos;ll attach a patch for the TestWordDelimiterFilter testcase which reproduces that issue shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
